    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently, there's no way to tell neovim not to show progress messages in message area. This would be useful because third-party plugins can listen to the `Progress` event and show the progress status in their own way. But currently, it'd lead to the progress message being shown twice. Once by the building message system and once by the plugin.\n\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo concrete solution yet. Creating issue to discuss on this.\nPossible ideas:\n- progress message format as an option\n- some way to provide a formatter function like (`vim.ui.progress_fmt`)\n- special field in progress that provides the signal (`handled_by`)",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Considering #35428 and future extui integration, I would think something like `set messageopt+=progress:none/statusline/cmd/msg'` could make sense.\n\nEDIT:\nI believe we have previously established that configurable message \"targets\" based on kind would be desirable for extui. So on second thought it may be best to lump this into an option mapping _all_ message kinds to a target, rather than just `progress`.",
